This README file contains information on the contents of the
meta-openrnd layer.

Please see the corresponding sections below for details.


Dependencies
============

This layer depends on:

  URI: git://git.openembedded.org/bitbake
  branch: master

  URI: git://git.openembedded.org/openembedded-core
  layers: meta
  branch: master

Patches
=======

Please submit any patches against the meta-openrnd layer to the
maintainer:

Maintainer: Maciej Borzecki <maciej.borzecki@open-rnd.pl>


Table of Contents
=================

  I. Adding the meta-openrnd layer to your build
 II. Misc


I. Adding the meta-openrnd layer to your build
=================================================

In order to use this layer, you need to make the build system aware of
it.

fAssuming the meta-openrnd layer exists at the top-level of your yocto
build tree, you can add it to the build system by adding the location
of the meta-openrnd layer to bblayers.conf, along with any other
layers needed. e.g.:

  BBLAYERS ?= " \
    /path/to/yocto/meta \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-yocto \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-yocto-bsp \
    /path/to/yocto/meta-meta-openrnd \
    "


